# BTRS Agents -- Cursor Instructions

See **AGENTS.md** for the full BTRS instruction set. This file adds Cursor-specific patterns.

## Setup

### Option 1: Global (all projects)

Copy BTRS to your Cursor global rules directory:

```bash
# Clone BTRS
git clone https://github.com/btrs-ai/btrs.git ~/.btrs

# Copy this file to your global Cursor rules
cp ~/.btrs/.cursorrules ~/.cursorrules

# Or symlink it so updates are automatic
ln -sf ~/.btrs/.cursorrules ~/.cursorrules
```

Then in any project, reference agents with `@~/.btrs/agents/btrs-architect/AGENT.md`.

### Option 2: Per-project

Clone into your project root:

```bash
git clone https://github.com/btrs-ai/btrs.git .btrs-agents
```

The `.cursorrules` file auto-loads. Reference agents with `@.btrs-agents/agents/btrs-architect/AGENT.md`.

## How to Use BTRS in Cursor

### Loading Agent Context
Use @file to load agent instructions as context:
- `@agents/btrs-architect/AGENT.md` -- for architecture work
- `@agents/btrs-api-engineer/AGENT.md` -- for backend APIs
- `@agents/btrs-web-engineer/AGENT.md` -- for frontend work
- `@agents/btrs-database-engineer/AGENT.md` -- for database/schema work
- `@agents/btrs-qa-test-engineering/AGENT.md` -- for testing
- `@agents/btrs-code-security/AGENT.md` -- for security review
- `@AGENTS.md` -- universal instructions (load this first)

See AGENTS.md for the full list of 24 agents.

### Using Composer
When using Composer for multi-file changes:
1. Load `@AGENTS.md` for conventions and verification protocol
2. Load the relevant agent's AGENT.md for domain expertise
3. Describe what you want -- the agent instructions guide the response
4. Review the plan, then approve

### Using @codebase
For broad searches or understanding project structure:
- @codebase works well for finding existing patterns and utilities
- Always check existing patterns before creating new ones

## Conventions (from AGENTS.md)
1. Check `.btrs/conventions/registry.md` before creating new components or utilities
2. Follow the 5-point verification protocol after changes
3. Match existing codebase patterns exactly
4. Update `.btrs/` vault files after completing work (code-map, todos, changelog)
